---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
---

<CaseStudyLayout org="Audible" role="Director, User Experience" year="2021–2023">

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Context</span>
    <h2 class="cs-section-title">A flagship product losing momentum</h2>
    <p>Audible's app was perceived by users as "stale and stagnant." Content discovery was broken, and Audible Originals — a key strategic differentiator — represented only 10% of listening activity despite being a top business priority. Internally, competing success metrics, team silos, and inefficient processes meant feature improvements took 6–9 months to ship.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">My Scope</span>
    <div class="cs-scope-grid">
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Team</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">12-person cross-functional squad (Design, Engineering, Product, Data Science, QA)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Reporting</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">Director of UX — peer to Product and Engineering directors</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Org Placement</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">Central product design org, embedded within mobile experiences</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-scope-item">
        <span class="cs-scope-label">Influence</span>
        <span class="cs-scope-value">Defined the squad operating model, later adopted by two additional business units</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Strategic Challenge</span>
    <h2 class="cs-section-title">Organizational structure was the product problem</h2>
    <p>The real blocker wasn't design quality — it was how teams were organized. Competing KPIs across siloed teams created misaligned incentives. No single group owned the end-to-end user experience. Features were designed in isolation, reviewed through disconnected approval chains, and shipped slowly. The product suffered not from a lack of ideas, but from a delivery model that couldn't execute on them.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Strategic Moves</span>
    <ul>
      <li>Championed and stood up a dedicated cross-functional squad — a new operating model at Audible — with embedded Design, Engineering, Product, and Data Science under unified leadership</li>
      <li>Partnered with Product leadership to establish a shared design vision built on four pillars: emerging business models, streamlined discovery, modernized visual language, and personalization</li>
      <li>Drove a rapid experimentation cadence — 12 A/B tests in a single quarter — replacing slow waterfall releases with validated, incremental delivery</li>
      <li>Established pulse surveys to track team health and demonstrated measurable sentiment improvement, building organizational evidence for the model</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Impact</span>
    <div class="cs-metrics">
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">+3.5%</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">Total revenue</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">+14%</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">Originals listening</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">36%</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">Faster than projected delivery</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cs-metric">
        <span class="cs-metric-value">2 BUs</span>
        <span class="cs-metric-label">Adopted the squad model within 9 months</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>Beyond metrics, the squad model became proof that design-led organizational change could accelerate product delivery. Leadership cited it as a template for future team structures across Audible.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <span class="cs-section-label">Selected Visual Evidence</span>
    <div class="cs-visuals">
      <div class="cs-visual">
        <img src="/images/projects/audible-tile.png" alt="Audible app redesign — home experience" />
        <span class="cs-visual-caption">Redesigned home experience with elevated content discovery and Originals positioning</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</CaseStudyLayout>
